issue.title: test: use MiniWallet for mempool_package_onemore.py
issue.body: This PR enables one more of the non-wallet functional tests (mempool_package_onemore.py) to be run even with the Bitcoin Core wallet disabled by using the MiniWallet instead, as proposed in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/20078. For this purpose helper methods `MiniWallet.{create,send}_self_transfer_multi` are introduced which serve as a replacement for `chain_transaction`. With this, it should be also quite straight-forward to change the larger related test `mempool_packages.py` to use MiniWallet.
